{
  "stem": "7337.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when we got out there, this whole camp was manned by Hitler Youth.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They were about 16 or 17 years old, and they were all in Nazi uniforms.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And the rules were that we got bread and water twice a day.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And for exercise, morning and afternoon, we-- we had to run in a circle, like-- like circus horses are trained.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the Nazis used to stand in the center with those long whips, except that they hit you properly, not-- didn't touch you, but hit you, so that you would run faster.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were not allowed to talk to each other.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A couple hours.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And kids used to faint.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We weren't used to this sort of exercise.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, every morning, they pulled a name out of the-- out of a box.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that boy was put into the middle of the swamp, and we had to stand in a half circle and see him sink.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that took over two hours.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's a scene that has been with me all my life-- that every day, one boy of my age was killed, was drowned, until he disappeared.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I think that it was less frightening to see what was happening than the thought as to whose name would be drawn for tomorrow, because it was quite obvious it might be your name.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this went on for over two months.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One boy a day.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at the end of June, I think it was the 21st of June, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] without saying anything, they loaded us into trucks again, those that were left, and put us back into cattle trucks, and took us back to a siding outside Berlin and unloaded us.",
      "word_count": 50
    }
  ],
